teed Rate Field has appeared in films such as ''[[Rookie of the Year (film)|Rookie of the Year]]'' (1993), ''[[Major League II]]'' (1994), ''[[Little Big League]]'' (1994), ''[[My Best Friend's Wedding]]'' (1997), and ''[[The Ladies Man (2000 film)|The Ladies Man]]'' (2000). In ''Rookie of the Year'' the stadium played the role of [[Dodger Stadium]] and in ''Little Big League'' the stadium played the role of all opposing ballparks except for [[Yankee Stadium (1923)|Yankee Stadium]] and [[Fenway Park]]. Commercials for the [[PGA Tour]], [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]], [[Reebok]] and the [[Boys & Girls Clubs of America]] have been filmed at the park.\n\n==Notes==\n*Nathaniel Whalen, \"Marked seats meaningful to Sox stars\", Post Tribune, March 30, 2007\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Baseball|Chicago}}\n*[[Gene Honda]] \u2013 Public address announcer for the White Sox, [[DePaul Blue Demons men's basketball|DePaul Basketball]], [[Chicago Blackhawks]] and the [[NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Championship]] Final Four.\n*[[Roger Bossard]] \u2013 Head groundskeeper for the White Sox. (1983\u2013present)\n*[[Nancy Faust]] \u2013 Long-time stadium organist for the White Sox. (1970\u20132010)\n*[[Southpaw (Chicago White Sox mascot)|Southpaw]] \u2013 White Sox mascot.\n*[[Camelback Ranch]] \u2013 The spring training home of the White Sox shared with the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]]. (2009\u2013present)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://chicago.whitesox.mlb.com/cws/ballpark/ Stadium site on whitesox.com]\n*[http://www.isfauthority.com/ ISFAuthority.com]\n*[http://www.andrewclem.com/Baseball/USCellularField.html Andrewclem.com]\n*[http://www.ballparksofbaseball.com/al/USCellularField.htm Ballparksofbaseball.com]\n*[http://www.ballparks.com/baseball/american/comis2.htm Ballparks.com]\n*[http://www.bing.com/maps/default.aspx?v=2&FORM=LMLTCP&cp=qz4f727pxfmc&style=b&lvl=1&tilt=-90&dir=0&alt=-1000&phx=0&phy=0&phscl=1&scene=11399796&encType=1 Aerial vie